FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1773342677
OL,3,CResidents take legal action over
OL,4,Cpotential cancer-causing contamination
OL,5,Crisk
OL,7,FWyre Council and the Environment
OL,8,FAgency have closed two allotments in
OL,9,FThornton-Cleveleys as part of an
OL,10,Finvestigation into potential historic
OL,11,Fcontamination that may increase the
OL,12,Frisk of cancer.
OL,14,FResidents have been told not to eat
OL,15,Fany produce grown on the allotments on
OL,16,FOccupation Road and Sandringham Avenue.
OL,18,FThey are due to meet with Wyre Council
OL,19,Fthis evening after the area may have
OL,20,Fbeen contaminated with a carcinogenic
OL,21,Fchemical.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1773342677
OL,3,CResidents take legal action over
OL,4,Cpotential cancer-causing contamination
OL,5,Crisk
OL,7,FAlthough the majority of properties
OL,8,Ftested showed concentrations of
OL,9,Fperfluorooctanoic acid, or PFOA, at a
OL,10,Flevel considered to require no further
OL,11,Faction, a small number may need
OL,12,Ffurther assessment to determine
OL,13,Fwhether additional steps are necessary.
OL,15,FFurther data has been received as part
OL,16,Fof the continuing investigation into
OL,17,Fhistoric contamination linked to
OL,18,FHillhouse Technology Enterprise Zone
OL,19,Fin Thornton.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1773342677
OL,3,CResidents take legal action over
OL,4,Cpotential cancer-causing contamination
OL,5,Crisk
OL,7,FIt comes two years after a multi-
OL,8,Fagency investigation was launched in
OL,9,F2024 to examine potential historic
OL,10,Fcontamination by the chemical
OL,11,Fperfluorooctanoic acid (PFOA) from
OL,12,Fpart of the former ICI site, now
OL,13,Foperated by AGC Chemicals Europe Ltd.
OL,15,FThe substance was used in
OL,16,Fmanufacturing processes at the site
OL,17,Fand released into the air between the
OL,18,F1950s and 2012.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1773342677
OL,3,CResidents take legal action over
OL,4,Cpotential cancer-causing contamination
OL,5,Crisk
OL,7,FAGC Chemicals Europe, Ltd, says that
OL,8,Fwhile PFOA was used in its
OL,9,Fmanufacturing processes, this was
OL,10,Fvoluntarily phased out by 2012."
OL,12,FThe International Agency for Research
OL,13,Fon Cancer (IARC) has now classified
OL,14,FPFOA) as cancer-causing, or
OL,15,Fcarcinogenic (Group 1).
OL,26,@rD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/10
